    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The village incorporated in 1931 to keep local control over land use and curb suburban development pressures.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        10
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/baxter_estates_new_york"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The Baxter Homestead, built in 1673, stood at 15 Shore Road until a 2017 fire destroyed it, though it was a 2005 historical landmark.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baxter_Estates%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Port Washington’s first public library opened in 1895 inside the Baxter Homestead and now sits within Baxter Estates on Main Street.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
